post_text:
According to Keep America Beautiful,
PPE litter has been on the rise. Please keep your gloves, masks, and disposable wipes out of our streets, green spaces, waterways, and parking lots, and put them in a trash receptacle instead. You might also consider utilizing reusable options, or signing our pledge against litter at keepgeorgiabeautiful.org. #reconsiderlitter #ShareRockdaleGA #KAB #KCRB
( Robin Benzrihem)

post_text:
The next Rockdale County Planning and Zoning Meeting will take place on Tuesday, June 23 at 9 a.m. and will be followed by Board of Commissioners Meeting at 10 a.m. in the Rockdale County Auditorium, located at 903 Main Street, Conyers, GA 30012.

The meetings will be open to the public and will abide by guidelines set to reduce the spread of COVID-19, which include social distancing and encouraging attendees to wear masks. The doors will open to the public
as early as 8:45 a.m. In-person public comment will be available for both meetings.

The meetings will also be streamed live on the Rockdale County Facebook page. Afterwards, the recording will be placed on Vimeo and Youtube for on-demand listening. To access it, the public can go to vimeo.com/rockdalegov or youtube.com/rockdalegov.

To see the agenda for the upcoming meeting, residents can click here: https://rockdalecountyga.gov/our-government/board-of-commissioners/board-of-commissioners-meeting-agendas/

For more information, please contact Jennifer Rutledge at jennifer.rutledge@rockdalecountyga.gov.

Everyone reacts differently to stressful situations like COVID-19. You may feel anxiousness, anger, sadness, or overwhelmed. Find ways to reduce your stress to help yourself and the people you care about.
• Learn the common signs of stress.
• Make time to unwind and do activities you enjoy.
• Talk with family and friends by phone, text, or email.
• If you or a loved one is feeling overwhelmed, get support 24/7 by calling 1-800-985-5990 or text TalkWithUs to 66746.
Learn more about stress and coping during the COVID-19 outbreak: https://bit.ly/39UVoEj

Everyone reacts differently to stressful situations like COVID-19. You may feel anxious, mad, sad, or overwhelmed. Find ways to reduce your stress to help yourself and the people you care about.

-Learn the common signs of stress.
-Make time to unwind and do activities you enjoy.
-Talk with family and friends by phone, text, or email.

If you or a loved one is feeling overwhelmed, get support 24/7 by calling 1-800-985-5990 or text TalkWithUs to 66746.
